@DipeshGopal - teach us about signs of metastasis!
- instead of bemoaning our access to lab reports prior to apts, prepare us for them and teach us how to understand them
- support programs that teach patients to understand research

@DipeshGopal - take dense breasts seriously, adjust monitoring accordingly, bring it up instead of us bringing it up
- treat prognosis as an important part of our ability to plan our future and not a side note if/when we end active treatment
- treat us as collaborators not subjects

@DipeshGopal - structure your practices at all levels to reflect that men (cis and trans) and non-binary people get breast cancer 
- train your staff in an ongoing way about how to treat patients with respect and dignity
- train self and staff about diversity (race, sexual orientation, etc.)

